Sanctimonious refers to a [[hypocritical]] form of excessive [[piety]], considered to be an affectation merely for public show.  Similar terms are [[self-righteous]], [[phony]], [[holier-than-thou]].

==Examples==

Some commentators have cited the congressional action of [[Tom DeLay]] and [[President George W. Bush]] regarding the [[Terri Schiavo]] affair as an example of sanctimonious behavior, where extraordinary legislation was passed to save a life at the same time they are enacting legislation that would deny [[Medicaid]] benefits to numerous patients in similar predicaments.

